00:15:27.020 --> 00:15:28.680
And in fact, that's
not the answer.

00:15:28.680 --> 00:15:31.670
The answer is, in fact, there
is zero, absolutely zero

00:15:31.670 --> 00:15:33.880
probability of finding
a electron here.

00:15:33.880 --> 00:15:37.100
So basically we're saying yes,
we can go from point a to

00:15:37.100 --> 00:15:39.990
point c without ever going
through point b.

00:15:39.990 --> 00:15:42.180
That might seem confusing
if you're thinking about

00:15:42.180 --> 00:15:45.430
particles, but remember we're
talking about the wave-like

00:15:45.430 --> 00:15:47.000
nature of electrons.

00:15:47.000 --> 00:15:51.310
So, the quantum mechanical
interpretation is that we can,

00:15:51.310 --> 00:15:55.820
